	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Fenin~<BR>
<BR>
I think you yourself should stop spreading mis-information.<BR>
<BR>
First of all, I'm L50 and all the named gnolls in Paw are blue.  There is no way the gnoll that drops the tome is green to you, unless you are L51+, so please stop with the lies.<BR>
<BR>
Second, the only &quot;common&quot; drop from any of the named gnolls in Paw is the summon corpse scroll and brains from the Ishva Mal.  All the other named gnolls drop items, but the drop is RARE.  I've killed this gnoll many, many times and I'd say on average the tome is a 1 in 8 drop.<BR>
<BR>
Third, if you think your going to be Fear kiting this gnoll, you are an even bigger liar.  Its not tough for a L50 necro to solo Rosch Val, but you shouldn't be using Fear unless you intend on pulling a nice train on yourself.  All the named gnolls are very resistant to root/darkness.<BR>
<BR>
As far as its value, consider its a rare drop, and that the gnoll that drops it is a 4 hour spawn.  This makes the tome drop only a few times per week.  Before many ppl knew about it, I had this gnoll all to myself for a week and in that time collected 3 tomes out of about 20 kills.  Its also the only other held item that gives +10 int besides the stein.<BR>
<BR>
 Considering all of this, the value of it still varies greatly.  I've personally traded one straight up for a gold chitin bracer, and another for a cowl (plus I threw in 1k plat).  However, I don't believe its worth an SMR.
				</font>
			</td>

